create task source info desc:
Select the object to be migrated this time from the upstreams that have been added. Replication config can adjust performance-related parameters, which generally do not need to be modified. Incremental migration tasks need to specify the migration start location. Two methods are supported:
1. Specify the binlog location for each upstream when creating a task. If there is a master-slave switch in the upstream, it must be filled in as GTID;
2. When creating a task, leave the position blank, and select "Create only" at the end, then start the task in the task list and select the start time.

create task target info desc:
Fill in the connection information of the downstream TiDB database. Please note:
1. DM will create a metadata database downstream, please make sure that the account you fill in has the corresponding permissions;
2. If using a domain name, please ensure that the host where the DM cluster is located has been configured properly with a DNS server;
3. Password supports filling in plain text or using `dmctl encrypt` encrypted password string;
4. Please check that the network firewall has opened the corresponding IP and port.
